                    <span class="alert-color"><strong>HCPS SCHOOLS CLOSED</strong><br><br>
It is with great sadness and disappointment that I share that in compliance with Governor Northam’s orders Halifax County Public Schools (and all schools within the Commonwealth) will be closed for the remainder of the 2019-2020 school year.<br><br>

A few guarantees that Halifax County Schools will make to the public and our stakeholders are below. First in respect to closing out the school year: If at all possible, we will continue on with some of the things we hold most dear: The relationship our educators have with our children. You can expect our educators to stay in touch with families on a regular basis in the months ahead. We will call, send emails, and use social media to provide instructional guidance and opportunities for you and your children. We will continue to meet the needs of our families in crisis through our federal lunch program. We will do everything in our power to continue the traditions of our school system: Our Comets of the Class of 2020 will walk across the stage at some date in the future. To the families of all of our students and to our dedicated staff starting last week, we began to prepare for what school may look like in the future if the COVID-19 virus continues into summer and fall. In short, we will have a plan in place going into the summer and a comprehensive approach to educating all of our students for the fall of 2020.<br><br>

In closing, we are here with you! We will provide frequent updates in the immediate future and throughout the summer. However, more than anything, our greatest desire is for Halifax County students and citizens to be safe. Stay well!<br><br>

Dr. Mark Y. Lineburg Superintendent<br>
Halifax County Public Schools</span><br><hr>
<p>For Coronavirus (COVID-19) Updates and FAQs, please visit our <a class="alert-color" href="https://www.halifax.k12.va.us/coronavirus">Coronavirus Information</a> page.</p>
        <hr>
<p>At Halifax County Public Schools, we are taking any threat seriously. If you feel unsafe or know of someone who feels unsafe, you can report it with this <a href="https://docs.google.com/forms/d/e/1FAIpQLSdni0zpLFeEX1DTsxBf3fEosxV5JPf_lM0XLVim8-3N7ideaQ/viewform">Threat Form</a>.</p>
        <hr>
<p>The community is invited to participate in discussions about the proposal to renovate/rebuild the High School. Please visit the <a href="http://www.halifax.k12.va.us/facilitystudy">High School Facility Study</a> page for more details.</p>
    </div>
</div>
