<p>Good afternoon.  Halifax County Middle School will be sending a google form to all parents today by email and text message.  The form will ask parents to verify which option(s) their child will choose to finish out the 19-20 school year.  The options are as follows.</p>
<strong><p> </p></strong><p>Option 1: Parent or guardian accepts the third nine weeks grade as posted on Friday, April 10, based on work completed before March 13. * No further action is needed by the student, or the parent or guardian, with regard to the 2019-20 school year grades if they choose Option I. </p>
<strong><p></p></strong><p>Option 2: Students can improve their final Term 3 grade by completing optional recovery assignments assigned by their teacher.  Improvement in Term 3 grades for HCMS students may improve the student’s year-long average.  These opportunities will be provided by teachers beginning April 27.  In some cases, teachers may choose to consider work that has already been assigned, completed, and submitted during the closure.  Students must complete and submit all recovery assignments as assigned by their teachers, by Friday, May 8, at 4 p.m. *Participation in the optional recovery plan can only improve a student’s grade.  Student grades will not decrease based on work completed as part of the optional recovery plan. *If Option 2 is selected, students should check their Google Classroom and email every day for assignments.  If internet access is not available, please select that option on the google form and contact your child’s teacher.</p>
<strong><p> </p></strong><p>IMPORTANT:  In order to be promoted to the next grade, a student must pass ALL core classes and two semesters of related arts with a final grade of 70 or above.</p>
<p>Parents may verify their student’s up to date average in T3 Term Grade on Parent Portal. The form needs to be completed and returned by Friday, April 17, 2020.  If you do not have the correct email in Infinite Campus, please email <a target="_blank" rel="nofollow">dmiller@halifax.k12.va.us</a> <strong></strong>and the form will be sent to you. It is very important that we receive this information for every student.  <strong></strong></p>
<strong></strong><p>Thank you,</p>
